Who will win prizes, and who will get the penalty?

main.title: Episode #410 â€“ Mission Impossible
main.post: M Agency versus R Agency. Tom Cruise, Simon Pegg and Henry Cavill join Running Man this week for a thrilling episode of cat and mouse. The Running Man cast trans-form into secret agents for R Agency. Among them, there are three spies working for M Agency. Will the R Agency agents find out who those three spies are, or will M Agency succeed in their infiltration and catch the R Agency leader?

main.title: Episode #411 â€“ Missing Shoes
links.post: Where did Jong Kookâ€™s shoes go? One of the Running Man members has a personal vendetta against Jong Kook and stole his shoes as a way to get back at him. The members play various games in order to get hints as to who this petty thief is. Seok Jinâ€™s strange behavior puts him at the top of that list. Who is the real petty thief? Will the members figure out who that person is?

links.title: Episode #412 â€“ 8 Race
links.post: This week, it is the eight-year anniversary of Running Man. To commemorate such a wonderful day, the Running Man members are once again given missions. This time, it is related to the number â€˜eightâ€™. The members are divided into teams, and each team has a distinct mission. For these missions, they need to call in guests. The first 3 members who get all the 8s can move onto the finals. Who will gain victory?

links.title: Episode #413 â€“ Unlucky Vacation
links.post: For this week, the Running Man members go on a vacation. However, not only is it a vacation, but it is an â€˜Unlucky Vacationâ€™. The members are divided into two teams, and among them, the unlucky ones and the lucky ones partner up. Every time a team wins, they receive one point and also the right to pick a penalty for the losing team. Will the lucky members be able to live up to their name? Or will the unlucky members regain their honor?

links.title: Episode #414 â€“ Suspicious Race
links.post: For this week, the Running Man members are called by the staff one by one as soon as the shooting begins. They are told to pick a member to whom they will give half of their Running Money. Since having the most money puts them at an advantage, all the members start playing mind games all of a sudden. Meanwhile, Kim Roi Ha, Kwak Si Yang, and Seo Hyo Rim join them as the best villains and villainess.

links.title: Episode #415 â€“ Birthday Race
links.post: Jae Seok, Haha, and Ji Hyoâ€™s birthdays are in August. For this week, Seok Jin, Jong Kook, Se Chan, So Min, and Kwang Soo are called in and told to choose between a birthday cake and a birthday punch. They are divided into teams by their choices, and each team is given an opposite goal. The failing team will suffer an incredible penalty. Which team will fail with their mission? Stay tuned to find out!

links.title: Episode #416 â€“ Dangerous Choice (1)
links.post: This week, the staff asks each of the members to write down the other membersâ€™ secrets. While some of them are hesitant to reveal some secrets, claiming that disclosing them could force the members to retire, others immediately jot down sentences after sentences. Afterward, they are asked to participate in a game of Truth or Dare.

links.title: Episode #417 â€“ Dangerous Choice (2)
links.post: This week, the couple race continues. Little do they know, however, there is a huge secret hidden in todayâ€™s race. The couples are shocked to find out that their seemingly meaningless actions have brought upon great consequences. Now, they are desperate more than ever to break free from the race. What is the secret behind this race?

links.title: Episode #418 â€“ Dangerous Delivery (1)
links.post: This week, the Running Man members are given a mission to deliver a briefcase within six hours. If they successfully deliver it within the given time, only one of them will face the penalty. If they fail, everyone except for one of them will face the penalty. They are also banned from opening the briefcase, and if they decide not to listen, they will automatically fail the mission and will be given the penalty.

links.title: Episode #419 â€“ Dangerous Delivery (2)
links.post: This week, the Running Man members will finally be able to find out the secret behind the briefcase they tried their best to deliver last week. The briefcase has a three-digit passcode, and through various missions, the members will receive hints regarding the passcode. Furthermore, Jang Do Yeon joins them as a host and a mysterious woman who is in charge of the briefcase. What is the hidden truth behind this briefcase?

links.title: Episode #420 â€“ Dangerous Delivery (3)
links.post: Last week, Jae Seok and Seok Jin received the Blank Penalty Ticket which means they will be sent on a penalty trip and will have to successfully carry out their mission in order to return. Meanwhile, for those who have won last weekâ€™s race, they are awarded the chance to go on a trip. What kinds of shocking surprises await the members this week?

links.title: Episode #421 â€“ Dangerous Delivery (4)
links.post: The race is not over yet! In order to complete their mission of 100, Jae Seok and Seok Jin have been doing various and random part-time jobs such as cycling and cleaning see-through floors. This time, they go net fishing, and Kwang Soo tags along as well. Meanwhile, Team Seoul is having a hard time finishing their vacation plans.

links.title: Episode #422 â€“ Donâ€™t Trust Her
links.post: This week, the Running Man members are divided into two teams, Team Voice and Team Face. Lee Ha Na and Im Soo Hyang join as captains for each team. Todayâ€™s mission has three rounds, and the team with more money left at the end will gain victory. Although it is a team game, individuals with the most amount of money left will also have an advantage. Will there be betrayals once again?

links.title: Episode #423 â€“ Game of Thrones
links.post: This week, it is all about ranks. First, the members turn a roulette that has all their names on it to decide who will be the first person to decide on the rankings. They will go through various missions and answer questions in order to change the order of the rankings. Meanwhile, one of them knows the answers to all the questions. If the other members can find out who this absolute member is, he or she will be put in last place and receive a penalty. Who is this absolute member, and who will be the ultimate winner?

links.title: Episode #424 â€“ The Nightmare of Halloween
links.post: This weekâ€™s race is called Dangerous Invitation that will unite ghosts from the East and West. With Son Na Eun, Seo Young Hee, and Ahn Hyo Seop joining as guests, the members show up wearing different costumes and makeups of famous characters from dramas and movies to celebrate Halloween. Then, the members and guests are divided into two teams, Team Humans and Team Ghosts, and play three missions. Winning members receive a hint that will lead them to win this weekâ€™s race. Stay tuned to find out the ultimate winner.

links.title: Episode #425 â€“ Dangerous Family
links.post: This week, the members of Running Man goes on a race called Go, Determined Gourmet. They must figure out which dish is the correct answer according to the hints they receive from completing the missions. Will the members be able to inherit the fortune from their dad?

links.title: Episode #426 â€“ Intimate Strangers
links.post: The members of Running Man have been together for eight years now. But how well do they know about each other? This week, the members must choose the most suitable person to carry out the mission presented to them. If everyone succeeds, itâ€™s a happy ending. If not, a penalty awaits the members.

links.title: Episode #427 â€“ Crazy Partners
links.post: Now that every one has found themselves a partner, it is time to begin the race. However, the members are informed that there are thieves among them. The thieves must not fail the missions if they donâ€™t want their identity revealed. Throughout the race, some of them will be given the chance to switch partners. Who will be the one to win the race in the end?

links.title: Episode #428 â€“ Everyone Has a Secret
links.post: This week, the members of Running Man begin the race to find the perfect food pairing for kimchi. Joined by the members of TWICE, they will form teams based on their preference. The staff of Running Man conducted a survey on which food complements kimchi the most. The team to guess the food in first place will win the race.

links.title: Episode #429 â€“ 2018 Year End Special (1)
links.post: So Min and Ji Hyo start todayâ€™s race as team leaders. They will each pick two members for their teams and race to the destination. However, people other than So Min and Ji Hyo receive text messages that are different from the ones So Min and Ji Hyo received. There is another female team leader who is waiting for them.

links.title: Episode #430 â€“ 2018 Year End Special (2)
links.post: This week, So Min, Ji Hyo, and Si Young continue their race as team leaders. So Minâ€™s team continues their mission in Hong Kong while Ji Hyoâ€™s team prepares a meal for 100 people with Hahaâ€™s wife, Byulâ€™s help. Meanwhile, Si Youngâ€™s team challenges themselves by milking four bottles of sheep milk in Gangwon Province.

links.title: Episode #431 â€“ Christmas Special â€“ The Miracle of Christmas
links.post: This week, the final episode of Year End Special gets aired. So MinÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s team comes back to Korea after failing the mission while the other two teams successfully clear the mission. After that, a new race to celebrate Christmas gets ready. Special guests, Soo Young, Sung Hoon, Seon Hwa, Hye Bin, Chi Yeul, and Ha Na join the show to participate in the new race, Christmas Special.

links.title: Episode #432 â€“ Christmas Special â€“ Flirting Santa Claus
links.post: Seok Jin and Kwang Soo are finally given the chance to get their revenge at the members. As Furious Santas, their mission is to steal the membersâ€™ personal belongings. They must steal all of the items before the race ends if they want to avoid facing penalties.

links.title: Episode #433 â€“ RPG: Episode 1, The Great Beginning
links.post: For the first race of the new year, the members of Running Man will have to reach Level 10 in order to win. Throughout the race, the members must find quests that are scattered all over the ski resort and complete them in order to level up. Whoever reaches the highest level first will be awarded with an amazing prize.

links.title: Episode #434 â€“ RPG: Episode 2, The Secret of The Clans
links.post: Last week, the members of Running Man formed clans of two. Each member revealed the secret of their clan member. To win the race, they must protect the clanâ€™s secrets throughout todayâ€™s race. As they move on from quest to quest, they will be joined by amazing guests, including the All-Stars of KBL, Winner, Chungha, and Do Yeon of Weki Meki.

links.title:
Date: 26/06/2019Author: RM Channel (RMC) 0 Comments	
Episode #435 â€“ RPG: Episode 3, Catch Me If You Can
links.post: Last week, the members of Running Man were given badges according to their levels. However, they become aware that some of the levels have been fabricated. Among five of the guests that have been invited today, there is a forger who fabricated the levels. The members must get to the bottom of what happened.

links.title: Episode #436 â€“ RPG: Episode 4, The Last War
links.post:
Episode #436 â€“ RPG: Episode 4, The Last War
At last, the Level Up Race will come to an end as the winner will be decided today. Six guests have been invited and they have been randomly assigned with different levels. The members of Running Man will partner up with the guests and compete against each other to reach the highest level.

links.title: Episode #437 â€“ New Year Special: I Am The King
links.post: Four actors from â€˜Haechiâ€™ appear at the Running Man. Il Woo, So Min, and Seok Jin claim that they are the real king. Other members and the guests need to find the real king to keep the peace. However, some of them commit treason in a chaotic state of affairs. Stay tuned to find out who the real king is!

links.title: Episode #438 â€“ Ace versus Champion
links.post: In this episode, the members divide into two teams. Team Ji Hyo and Team Jong Kook are competing to get the chance to go to LA. Each team leaders present the itineraries to scout members to their teams. They play various games to take more slots in the roulette for the final game. Stay tuned to find out which team wins!

links.title: Episode #439 â€“ Survive To The End
links.post: In this episode, the members divide into two teams. Team Jae Seok and Team Jong Kook select Korean traditional food in order. As they move on to the next restaurant, their budget gets reduced. The teams get to cut a wire on the opponent teamâ€™s bomb as they clear each step. During the missions, members visit a special friend. Stay tuned to find out which team wins!

links.title: Episode #528 â€“ Jeju Island Special Part 2: Loser-Pays-All Group Tour
links.post: This week, Running Man finishes up the two-part special on Jeju Island. This time, they partner up with a member and arrive on the scene as different people who are about to take a packaged tour of the island. However, each course they take will cost money, and only five members will get to go on each packaged trip. The members left behind play games where the loser pays for the five out having a blast.

links.title: Episode #529 â€“ Journal of Old Restaurant
links.post: This week, Hoshi and Mingyu of SEVENTEEN, Nam Joo and Bo Mi of Apink, and two comedians, Kim Soo Yong and Nam Chang Hee, join the members to participate in Old Restaurant Race. They need to find old restaurants around Seoul and deduct as many years as possible from the sum of their age in order to win. Stay tuned to find out which team wins!
